## 📝 설계 패턴

### 패턴 1: 상태 머신

```rust
#[derive(Debug)]
enum State {
    Start,
    Processing { step: u32 },
    Complete { result: String },
    Error { reason: String },
}

fn transition(state: State, action: &str) -> Result<State, String> {
    match (state, action) {
        (State::Start, "begin") => Ok(State::Processing { step: 1 }),
        (State::Processing { step }, "next") if step < 3 => {
            Ok(State::Processing { step: step + 1 })
        }
        (State::Processing { step }, "next") if step == 3 => {
            Ok(State::Complete { result: String::from("Done") })
        }
        (_, "error") => Ok(State::Error { reason: String::from("Error") }),
        (s, a) => Err(format!("Invalid action {} in state {:?}", a, s)),
    }
}
```

### 패턴 2: 커맨드 처리

```rust
#[derive(Debug)]
enum Command {
    Move { x: i32, y: i32 },
    Scale { width: u32, height: u32 },
    Rotate { angle: f32 },
}

fn execute(cmd: Command) -> String {
    match cmd {
        Command::Move { x, y } => format!("Move to ({}, {})", x, y),
        Command::Scale { width, height } => format!("Scale to {}x{}", width, height),
        Command::Rotate { angle } => format!("Rotate by {}°", angle),
    }
}
```

### 패턴 3: 에러 처리 및 복구

```rust
#[derive(Debug)]
enum Result<T, E> {
    Ok(T),
    Err(E),
}

match operation() {
    Ok(value) if value > 0 => println!("positive: {}", value),
    Ok(value) => println!("non-positive: {}", value),
    Err(e) if e.recoverable => println!("recoverable error: {}", e),
    Err(e) => println!("fatal error: {}", e),
}
```

